    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="538"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d538">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/3343</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Irkutsk</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_HEL1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d538fn1">Sent via the Legation in China.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Omsk</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 24, 1918</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received December 5, 12.22
                        p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Consul <persName corresp="#p_TAR1">Thomson</persName>, Irkutsk, reports that
                        <persName>Volkov</persName> and <persName>Krasiemkov</persName> arrived
                    Irkutsk last Sunday for the purpose of persuading <persName corresp="#p_SGG1"
                        >Semenov</persName> recognize <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1"
                        >Kolchak</persName> government. <persName corresp="#p_SGG1"
                        >Semenov</persName> and part of his command expected Irkutsk. According to
                    Vice Consul <persName>Palmer</persName>, Ekaterinburg, Social Revolutionist
                    committee planning vigorous action against <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1"
                        >Kolchak</persName> government. Certain members of the committee state that
                    they would rather join with the Bolsheviks and fight <persName
                        corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName> than remain with <persName
                        corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName> and fight Bolsheviks. Personally I
                    believe if Czechs decide to hold western front the Social Revolutionist element
                    will remain inactive.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HEL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harris</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
